
[1]scolding

   SCOLDING, ppr.

   1. Railing with clamor; uttering rebuke in rude and boisterous
   language.

   2. a. Given to scolding.

   SCOLDING, The uttering of rude, clamorous language by way of rebuke or
                         railing; railing language.
